@fxulusoy I agree with @rabbah 
I think it will be better to address the problem in the script tweak-dockermachine.sh
by adding the mirror, or just ping which repo is up and use that one.

In https://github.com/openwhisk/openwhisk/issues/530 the change was made to relax the installed version of ansible (to v2.1.0.0-1) and in https://github.com/houshengbo/openwhisk/commit/7ab9a47c8c17cfa0adbd0549c5b66bcb601871f9#diff-eb553454a207e03d414e88d99e504148 the installed ansible was done via apt-get instead of pip (because "pip install on vagrant requires lots of dev packages as it wants to compile deps. we don't want that." per @domdom82).

so we may want to install both via apt-get but install a version earlier (v2.1.0.0-1) than the latest which was just released.

@csantanapr @houshengbo

@mdeuser @dubeejw I rebased and resolved conflicts from the tests added in #927. In the process I discovered that doing `go-cli/wsk --apihost <valid host> property get --apibuild` is not working and neither is the test which tries to access controller via `http`. Can you address these separately (https://github.com/openwhisk/openwhisk/issues/586) or send a pull request to my branch and I can merge here. Hence, there are three tests that use the python CLI instead.

I also eliminated one test that is redundant (checking that unset of multiple values works as expected).

PPG 945 approved.
